caption: Favorite thai spot in Silver Spring! And I’ve eaten a lot of good thai food up here. They’re always timely, have a very Covid-conscious pickup system, and really pay attention to little details in my orders. I’d say try their drunken noodles but honestly it’s all good lol. Also the portions are big! Usually 2 meals for me. Try them and tip them!

From the moment  you arrive in that restaurant  the personel give you a nice feeling. Very warm stuff, it is a nice restaurant to  pass time with friends and colleagues or with your date. yummy  cuisine, talented  chief cook and stuff, comfortable  pay and courteous  service. Highly recommended.
My Favorite
Nice ambience and very welcoming service. The meals were fresh and delightful. Will absolutely recommend this restaurant to friends and family. Affordable rates and big meals. Keep up the great work.

After trying the other nearby Thai restaurants in downtown Silver Spring area, I can easily say that Lamoon is the best when it comes to flavor, price, portions, and customer service. Their lunch deals are great—you should definitely check out their lunch special where you can select up to three “option of the day” side dishes for less than $10.  They also have the best curry and pad see eaw when compared to the other restaurants.
(Translated by Google) Very rich...  (Original) Muy rico...

This is certainly one of the best restaurants in the neighborhood. Anytime I visit this place I am profoundly happy. They manage their high  standard service and the topmost level of cooking  they provide. You definitely will enjoy this this place. Warmly  recommended.
The food and ambiance are fantastic and we’re always treated like family.
Honestly not the  best thai..ordered the pad see ew and it had an odd taste. Serving size is quite generous though so might try something else on the menu

I like to go with friends to this place with my warmest recommendations. I  go to this restaurant often. This recommendation is always successful. The the cooking is delicious and the team is welcoming and cooperative. Every time  we visit this place we have a pleasing time.  warmly recommended.

Last week was the first time we visited this fine restaurant. But It is obviously not the last. We enjoyed the evening very much with the courteous service, with the superb  food and booze and with the comfortable charge. We will surely come back soon.
food was very good and im pickey i mainly eat thai and this is my new favorite spot
Beat up on the outside. Inside was clean. Food was delicious. Service was quick. No complaints here! The tomyum soup was on point.
The food and service were ahead of our expectations. We surely loved the vibes of this restaurant. Fantastic spot to take the family out for lunch.
Some of the best Thai food I’ve ever had in the DC area. Highly recommend!

Definitely a great find in downtown Silver Spring! We went for lunch and ordered off the lunch special menu. A main course, soup/appetizer, and drink were only $11. We had pad Thai, Thai iced tea, and the Tom yum chicken soup soup and all were fantastic. Wait staff was very nice as well. I'll definitely be going back.
Ordered off Uber eats. The drunken noodles would have been soo good if they gave more chicken, and if it wasn’t too salty. I had to mix my dish with rice for that reason, but it was still good

Food was good and it wasn't busy though I could tell they had a lot of delivery orders. Service was good, not overbearing but anytime I needed a refill it was prompt without being asked. Appitizers and dishes came out hot and quickly and portions weren't huge but we're filling. Definitely found a place we want to keep coming.
The food was great. Ordered takeout, so no notes on service, but I'm sure that is good too. Highly recommend the green curry or drunken noodles. Very authentic to what I had in Thailand.
I dine here at least twice a month. The food is delicious. You must go and try if you like Thai food very authentic.

Excellent excellent excellent authentic thai food. I had the wings, pork skewers, pad woon sen, drunken noodle, shrimp spring rolls and everything I have tried has been absolutely delicious. I just returned from Thailand a few months back and the food here taste just like the food in Thailand. The services was absolutely impeccable. I will definitely be returning over and over again.

Delicious and authentic Thai food in the heart of downtown Silver Spring, across from the Safeway.  The exterior of the building is shabby, but inside it is lovely and the food is divine.  Don't pass on the summer rolls--one of our favorite appetizers!  ENJOY!
A very tasty food good service and reasonable price.

First time coming here and it was so delicious I do miss the previous market ( Thai Market ) but this place has brought back the same flavor of food and their customer service is awesome in addition they have a mini bar for football season. This will be one of my favorite spots back in Silver Spring area.
Great food

My wife and I have been patronizing this restaurant for ages, especially prior to the renovations and usually for take out.  Last night, I walked in about 6pm and tried to order 10 chicken kebabs and had to wait a full five minutes for someone to emerge from a crowded kitchen, when a young male staffer came out and told me that they were to busy to prepare that order for me in less than an hour.  There were only 3 diners in there and the place was as quiet as a church mouse.  I left disappointed and regret that I didn’t get his name and summon the owner because he did not appear to be interested in my business.  They’ll get one more shot at it before we take our biz elsewhere.
Miss the charm of the old store. Authentic and better quick food choices. Now they're just like everybody else in downtown silver Spring. ☹️
The service is constantly quick, excellent ambience, very nice staff members. Will eat here again when I am nearby.
Clean Thai restaurant
Great Food!
Love it but get there way before 9 pm
Food is great here.

HERBIVORE TAKE:. i actually dig this spot a lot.  a bit dark/dingy, so some of y'all would balk, but the cooking was great!  we had thai iced tea, spring rolls, Panang curry tofu, they made a larb tofu for us, pad see ew, vegetables in a garlic brown sauce (name?  it was awesome)  probably my go to spot in silver spring right now.  maybe the region.  thai kitchens seem to ebb and flow, so who knows

Lamoon is a hidden gem! When I first walked in, I quickly noticed there were no patrons so I was apprehensive about dining. I quickly checked the reviews then asked for a menu and placed an order for the Drunken Noodle Chicken dish. Wow, was it good! I took my food to go and couldn’t even make it past the block where the restaurant is located before I opened it up, sat on the stoop and devoured it. I highly recommend it and will I’ll be back!

Lamoon is a hidden gem - when I first walked in the restaurant which had no patrons on the evening I visited, I was apprehensive about dining there. After a quick check of their reviews, I decided to review the menu and give them a try. Wow, am I glad I did. I went with the Drunken Noodle Chicken dish. The service was quick - I took it to go and couldn’t even make it past the block where the restaurant sits before I opened it and I couldn’t stop eating. The flat egg noodles had the perfect amount of spice, the veggies were crispy and the chicken was well seasoned. What a delicious meal, I’ll be back!
Food great! Took too long to make part of our meal.
delicious thai and not expensive.
Food is great and reasonably priced. Service was good too.
Good homestyle Thai dishes here and take away

Really authentic and delicious Thai food. The pad woon sen was really spicy but so mouthwatering yummy. The drunken noodles had great flavor but the noodles didn't seem as good as Amina Thai. The yellow curry's sauce was pretty good but the chicken felt a little overcooked. The rice in the mango sticky rice was so creamy yet chewy in the most elegant way. Portion sizes felt a little small but overall very tasty! Possibly increase portion and pricing accordingly ;)
Great delicious food.

It's a new Thai Market. It was a carryout part of the Thai food store. The original counter, table are still the same. Food - same authentic Thai, although menu was expanded to include some desert and soup. The hours was also extended to 10 pm. More specific details. They don't have parking as of now due to construction next do, only on street. If you're not familiar with Silver Spring you probably would have a hard time to find it - look for Safeway and this place is across the street. My last visit I had Crispy Spring rolls and  Yen To Fu - seafood soup. This set me up for $18 I give it 5 rating although it's more like 4.8 now. Consider Ruang Khao and Charm Thai. Kao Thai is way overpriced to be here.
I love to grab sticky rice and grilled pork on the way to patrol around downtown Silver Spring. I also like the fried banana for a snack.
Food is excellent. It takes a few extra minutes for prep but the result is worth it. Very fresh and delicious. Decor is quite plain but don't let that stop you. Food is worth it.
Phone number doesn’t work or doesn’t exist and Uber eats delivery doesn’t respond.
The best restaurants

I really enjoyed the pad Thai. The Thai red curry was excellent, with delicious spices and rice on the side. I had never tried mango sticky rice before, but let me tell you it was really tasty. The contrast between theango and coconut was awesome!! Definitely coming back for more.
Best variety of thai food for an absurdly inexpensive price. Only thing you could improve is a lack of ambiance but the food more than makes up for it.
Great food, and the price is low. No beer though.
Tasty and authentic
Delicious food and wonderful service. Especially loved the eggplant and “pottery shrimp.”
Good food always
If you like Thai food, this is my new favorite. Everything on the menu is good and they have a lot of dishes I haven't seen at other Thai restaurants!
MmyvThai wife"s heaven. Good Jun Ta Fo.and other Thai Food.

I have been a regular of this establishment ever since they first opened, coming by 2-3 days out of the week, even before they became Lamoon. However, my patronage ends today. Today, I wanted to stop by to see what the lunch specials were.; but before I entered the restaurant, I stopped in front to check my phone.  A couple of feet away, there was a man and woman sitting on the steps having a conversation. I can hear the woman asking if "you have a problem with me?" I ignore her thinking that she is talking to the man. A few minutes later, she is in MY face asking if I had a problem with her? I am puzzled because I have never seen this woman a day in my life. I let her know that I am a customer. She then asks if I work at the establishment, to which I replied that I do not. Her response was, "you're lying!" I don't want any trouble, I just want to get my food and get the hell out of there, but she prevents me from entering the restaurant, accusing me of lying to her. She then opens the door and shoves me into the restaurant spewing obscenities. Once inside the restaurant, I ask the gentleman behind the register to call the police because the woman outside assaulted me. His response was, "I have nothing to do with that. If you want to call the police you can do that from your own phone." I'm upset at this point and I ask, "did you not see that woman shove me in here? Of course it's your business! She is harassing customers in front of your establishment!" The restaurant worker repeats himself saying, "we don't want to involve the police, do you understand that?" I say all this to say that I have been a REGULAR of this establishment since 2008. I expected a little more from the restaurant worker instead of just a shrug. I am Asian, by the way. Now had I been a WHITE woman who had gotten assaulted, I am QUITE sure they would have called the police on my behalf and at least ACTED like they cared...  I've attached pics of the assailant.  So if you see her, beware...she is very hostile and very violent.

Chicken Pad Thai was just ok. My husband got the Drunken noodles and said the chicken was rubbery and didn't eat anymore of the chicken from his dish. The place was clean but deserted for a Friday night.
Yen Ta For noodles soup is delicious and service is good.
One of the best places for authentic Thai food. 3-item combo for $9 is the best. Get to choose for a variety of premade entrees. Off-the-hook.
Doubling up my review from the other listing - excellent Thai place downtown Silver Spring!
Excellent and authentic Thai food!

Not a fan of this place. I ordered spring rolls and the drunken noodles with chicken. The spring rolls are the ONLY thing I liked here. My "drunken noodles" dish was lacking in sauce, it was greasy, and, what was supposed to be a fresh dish, had cold spots. Idk if they pre-made the noodles and cook the chicken per order, but when my dish came out it wasn't all the same temp. The chicken was also kind of rubbery. My friend ordered the papaya salad with crab meat and was served a salad with an undercooked 1/4 crab IN THE SHELL. He was expecting the crab MEAT to just be in the dish.

SO. DAMN. HAPPY. Should have come here sooner! After nearly giving up on Thai food on the East Coast, finally something akin to the awesome hole-in-the-wall Thai places I used to haunt back home on the West Coast! This place has everything you really want and need - AUTHENTIC, FLAVORFUL food (they passed my Pad Thai test — I can taste the tamarind!), low prices, clean, and quick. There are many options - a lunch bar with pre-made dishes that looked hot, fresh, and tasty; a menu with a decent number of things to choose from; and then some ‘home-made’ grab-n-go items that are awesome and authentic! The decor is simple, but it seems like it is being upgraded gradually as they get this business up and running. The family running the place are really nice, as well.  I’ll be back again soon. :)
Best Thai food in the area. Great Prices... Great Food!!!!

Great food.  The restaurant is still transitioning from a Thai grocery store adjunct to an independent restaurant.  You can either order off the menu or select already prepared entrees at the counter.   Service is informal.  While they offer table service, most patrons order at the counter.  Either way, it's probably the most authentic Thai food in the Silver Spring town center area.

This is the great little Thai food counter on the side of the former Thai Market which is unfortunately now closed. They have a daily selection of prepared entrees as well as items from a menu. My favorites are the crispy pork with chili sauce, roasted pork with eggs and tofu, and the grilled pork skewers with sticky rice. They also have the usual fish or chicken curries,  noodle soups, and a variety of sausage and rice dishes from the local community. There is not much atmosphere, it is a simple to go counter with about five rickety old tables to sit at with your styrofoam plates if dining in. But the food is excellent, the service is friendly, and the price is right.  If you like authentic food like you might get from the street vendors or markets in Thailand, give this place a try!
